Wrangle annotation data

a <- a |>
  mutate(state = str_extract(misc, "(?<=/)[^/]+(?=/)")) |>
  mutate(state = ifelse(state == "Memphis", "Tennessee", state)) |>
  select(-`...1`, -misc)

dist <- dist.dna(seqs, model = "K80")

Create tree object

# Neighbor-Joining 2.0
t <- bionj(dist)

# Neighbor-Joining
# Maximum Likelihood
# Minimum Evolution

Plot tree

# open tree in new window for optimal viewing
ggtree(t) +
  geom_tiplab()
! The tree contained negative edge lengths. If you want to ignore the edges,
you can set `options(ignore.negative.edge=TRUE)`, then re-run ggtree.

Add annotation data to the tree

p <- ggtree(t) %<+% a
! The tree contained negative edge lengths. If you want to ignore the edges,
you can set `options(ignore.negative.edge=TRUE)`, then re-run ggtree.

Add color to trees

library(viridis)
Loading required package: viridisLite
p + geom_tiplab(aes(color = year), size = 3) +
    scale_color_viridis_c() +
    theme_tree2()
p + geom_tiplab(aes(color = state), size = 3) +
    scale_color_hue(n = 15) +
    theme_tree2()
